## 🎯 HTMX Event System

### Why Events?

Traditional HTMX tightly couples components:

```html
<!-- Form MUST know about list -->
<form hx-post="/Todos/Create" hx-target="#todo-list">
</form>
```

**Swap events decouple everything:**

```html
<!-- Form doesn't know about list -->
<form hx-post="/Todos/Create" hx-swap="none"></form>

<!-- List listens independently -->
<div id="todo-list" 
     hx-get="/Todos/List"
     hx-trigger="ui.refreshList from:body">
</div>

<!-- Stats also listen (no form changes needed!) -->
<div id="stats"
     hx-get="/Todos/Stats"
     hx-trigger="ui.refreshList from:body">
</div>
```

### Event Chain Example

**Define events:**

```csharp
// Domain/Events/DomainEvents.cs
public static class DomainEvents
{
    public static string TodoCreated => "entity.created:todo";
    public static string TodoUpdated => "entity.updated:todo";
    public static string TodoDeleted => "entity.deleted:todo";
}
```

**Register chains:**

```csharp
// Web/Events/SwapEventChains.cs
events.Chain(
    DomainEvents.TodoCreated,
    "ui.refreshList",
    "ui.showToast");
```

**Fire from Application layer:**

```csharp
// Application/Services/TodoService.cs
_eventBus.Fire(DomainEvents.TodoCreated);
```

**Listen in views:**

```html
<div hx-get="/Todos/List"
     hx-trigger="ui.refreshList from:body">
</div>
```

